                   <h2 style="text-align: center;"><strong><em>Meet the Artist for March </em></strong></h2>
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><strong><em>Doug Jones</em></strong></h2>
<h2 style="text-align: left;"><strong><em></em></strong>&nbsp;</h2>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="assets/images/Image%20Bank%20for%20Branch%20Use/Lumby/Painted_Hills%20_3Poster.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="303" /></p>
<p style="text-align: left;" align="center"><strong><em></em></strong>&nbsp;</p>
<h2><em><em></em><strong><em>Innerscapes:&nbsp; </em></strong><strong><em>recent photographs from my archives</em></strong>&nbsp;</em></h2>
<h2 style="text-align: left;"><strong><em>Artist's Statement:</em></strong></h2>
<h2>&nbsp;</h2>
<h2>I believe that every person has a powerful but largely unconscious connection with the landscape, often of their childhood, and also of places where other significant events in their lives have occurred. My hope as an artist is that you, the viewer, will engage in a dialogue with my images, and make a personal&nbsp; connection with your own landscapes, memories, and emotions.</h2>
<h2>&nbsp;</h2>
<h2>I don&rsquo;t &lsquo;take&rsquo; photographs -- I discover them -- and then use that unique moment where the landscape, the light, and my presence intersect to create an image. Those moments don&rsquo;t happen by accident, however. I spend a lot of time scouting locations, going back repeatedly, and then waiting for the light. The images in this show began as film and digital records, and have only recently been printed from my archives</h2>
<h2>&nbsp;</h2>
<h2>Unlike some other artistic processes, photography requires the artist to be fully conscious in the present moment when the image is created. Nothing can be revised or conjured up later out of one&rsquo;s imagination. Because my work is about the landscape and my connection to it, photography is the ideal medium because it requires me to be fully present at the moment of creation.</h2>
<h2>&nbsp;</h2>
<h2>Most of my works have a very personal connotation for me; many are places I have visited repeatedly for rest, meditation, and inspiration. I often do not fully comprehend the personal meaning of the images I have made until long after the creative process is complete and the finished print is hanging on my wall.</h2>
<h2>&nbsp;</h2>
<h2>While form, texture, and composition are the basic language of expression in my work, my intent is to point the viewer toward a direct, personal, and unmediated experience that breaks down the boundaries between image and reality. For this reason, I call these works "<em>Innerscapes</em>", suggesting the inseparable connection between subject and object, the personal and universal.</h2>
<h2><strong>You may meet Doug, in the library,&nbsp;on April 2nd from 12:00 to 1:00 to inquire about his photographic processes and art work</strong>.</h2>
<p>___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________</p>
<h2 style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</h2>
<h2 style="text-align: left;"><img src="assets/images/Image%20Bank%20for%20Branch%20Use/Snowman.png" alt="" width="83" height="80" /><strong>Winter Story Time will begin January 14 - March 31</strong></h2>
<h2 style="text-align: left;"><strong>FREE program&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong></h2>
<h2><strong>Read, Build, Play </strong>is our NEW concept for Story time.</h2>
<h2>Thursdays at 11:30 - Drop in program</h2>
<h2 style="text-align: left;">Bringing play into our story time can assist in the early literacy component. The adults are invited&nbsp;to share in hands on activities after we read a story or two. Much of the focus will be on the alphabet and letter sounds. All materials are supplied.</h2>
<h2 style="text-align: left;">Each child will be given a booklet which is theirs to discover the alphabet through drawing, colouring and stickers.&nbsp;</h2>
<h2 style="text-align: left;">Duplo will be our play activity where we will&nbsp;build with the&nbsp;focus on the stories we read.</h2>
<p style="text-align: left;">___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________&nbsp;</p>
<h2><strong>Book Club</strong></h2>
<h2>Do you like to share your latest read and engage in lively discussions? Lumby Branch invites you to join us in starting a book club&nbsp;that would occur once per month. It is open ot all interested adults and preregistration is not required.&nbsp;A kettle and coffee maker&nbsp;can be provided. We would love to have you meet in our library and can order any books that you may require.&nbsp;The first book club meeting will be April 7th at 6:00 pm.</h2>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________</strong></p>
<h2><img src="assets/images/Image%20Bank%20for%20Branch%20Use/Westbank/Yarn_Sheep.jpg" alt="" width="106" height="122" /><strong>Common Threads </strong></h2>
<h2><strong>Thursdays to the end of June.</strong></h2>
<h2>The knitting program was so popular that people asked that it be extended in the New Year. We have not only extended the time from 3:00 - 4:30 but will add any needle craft. Come to the library to connect with like-minds. There is usually someone on hand to help with projects.&nbsp;</h2>
<h2 style="text-align: left;"><strong>_________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________</strong></h2>
<h2 style="text-align: left;"><strong></strong>&nbsp;<strong>Makerspace Tuesdays</strong></h2>
<h2 style="text-align: left;">Tuesdays in January, February and March<strong> </strong></h2>
<h2 style="text-align: left;"><strong>starts at 3:00 PM but can drop in anytime after as it is a self directed project - FREE PROGRAM</strong></h2>
<h2 style="text-align: left;">Come create a new project each month as we supply the materials and directions. We will have a new material to<strong> </strong>work with each month and you take your finished project home. Try your hand at a new skill.</h2>
<h2 style="text-align: left;">Registration is suggested due to supplies.</h2>
<h2 style="text-align: left;">March craft material is craft sticks. A new project each week.</h2>
<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>__________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________</strong></p>
<h2 style="text-align: left;"><strong>Tech Training </strong></h2>
<h2 style="text-align: left;"><strong>February to April</strong></h2>
<h2>Have a computer but struggling with basics such as searching the Internet, using email or Facebook? Need help navigating the ORL website or using some of our amazing electronic databases? Our library is offering one to one tutoring to help from February to April. You can sign up for these free sessions by calling the library at 250-547-9528.</h2>
<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>__________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________</strong></p>
<h2><strong>Adult Colouring Book Weekends</strong></h2>
<p><strong></strong>&nbsp;<img src="http://image.ie/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/034-1024x716.jpg" alt="" width="367" height="316" /></p>
<h2><strong>Saturdays</strong></h2>
<h2>Colour inside or outside the lines at our Colouring Book Weekends.&nbsp; Drop in; we'll have colouring sheets, pencil crayons and markers ready to go!&nbsp;&nbsp; Or feel free to bring in your own colouring books and crayons.&nbsp; Kids and teens are welcome too!&nbsp; And if you want to display your finished picture, we'll be happy to put&nbsp; it on display in the library.</h2>
